@rmader It was a random crash of the entire compositor in an almost out-of-the-box Fedora rawhide installation whilst using the Firefox (v69.0.1) web browser. I've only ever seen the problem once and perhaps it is as random as a race condition experienced once every 5 years. Unfortunately this doesn't look like an easy bug to reproduce.

!755 does look interesting. Is it possible for thread1 to cause the execution of `meta_wayland_surface_apply_pending_state` whilst `meta_surface_actor_wayland_dispose` is part-way through being executed by thread2? The backtrace shows that `meta_wayland_surface_apply_pending_state` (the function causing the segmentation fault) was called via `wl_event_loop_dispatch`.

I see at https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/mutter/blob/master/src/compositor/meta-window-actor.c#L1600 that `build_and_scan_frame_mask` checks the return vale of `meta_surface_actor_get_texture` for a NULL value, a check which is not done in the `meta_wayland_surface_apply_pending_state` function.
